cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.AI. 

The paper presents a state estimation pipeline for autonomous flight using event cameras, standard frames, and inertial measurements. This involves robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques for visual odometry and SLAM. The use of machine learning (cs.LG) is also mentioned in the paper for the training of the neural network used in the event camera processing. The system also involves control and optimization (cs.SY) for the quadrotor flight. Finally, the paper presents a novel approach to combining different types of sensors, which could be of interest to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) community.
